      "p_value": "p < 0.001",
      "confidence_interval": null,
      "verbatim_quote": "These lead us to distinguish three different time regimes, all of which are statistically significantly distinct at p < 0.001% (using bootstrap resampling): The weekend: Saturdays and Sundays, where the average acceptance rate is comparatively high at 23.5%. Typical non-working hours during the week: evenings after 4:00 pm PST until mornings 7:00 am PST, where the average acceptance rate is also rather high at 23%. Typical working hours during the week from 7:00 am PST to 4:00 pm PST, where the average acceptance rate is much lower at 21.2%."
